<p itemprop="description">A chief technology officer provides strategic leadership for technology across the organisation. They are responsible for technology strategy, innovation, and ensuring technology solutions align with business objectives and user needs.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Define and execute organisation-wide technology strategy and vision</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Lead digital transformation and technology innovation initiatives</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Build and manage high-performing technology teams</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Establish technology architecture standards and governance</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Drive adoption of modern technology practices and platforms</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Manage technology investments and vendor relationships</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Ensure technology solutions meet user needs and business objectives</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Represent the organisation in external technology forums</li>
    </ul>
</section>

